'''Arda Turan''' (born January 30, 1987), is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] [[association football|footballer]] playing for [[Galatasaray S.K.|Galatasaray]] and the [[Turkey national football team|Turkish national team]]. Already a regular in the [[Fatih Terim]]'s [[Turkey national football team|Turkish]] team at the age of 22, he currently has over 30 senior international caps. In July 2008, Arda was ranked 8th in the selection of the 100 Best Young Football Players in the World as published by [[Spain|Spanish]] magazine [[Don Bal<U+00F3>n]].<ref>[http://www.footballingworld.com/2009/03/31/who-on-earth-is-arda-turan-galatasaray-0244/: Who on earth is Arda Turan?]</ref>

==Club career==
===Galatasaray===
He is a product of the Galatasaray youth system, but initially came to light once being on loan to [[Manisaspor]] in the 2005&ndash;06 season. He was recalled the for the start of the following season, and made a regular start in the first team. It was during this time that he received his first senior international call up. Arda quickly impressed manager [[Eric Gerets]] with his performances early in the 2006&ndash;07 season. After his performances in the [[UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] qualifiers which led Galatasaray to the group stage, Arda became a first team regular. 

Arda continued his development in the 2007&ndash;08 season. Despite a poor start to the season, Arda improved his performances immensely, scoring seven goals in the second half of the season. He scored a hat-trick against [[Sivasspor]] on 4 May 2008. Following his impressive displays domestically, [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] made a <U+00A3>9m offer to buy Arda prior to the [[UEFA Euro 2008|Euro 2008]] championships, but the Galatasaray chairman rejected the offer.<ref>[http://www.sabah.com.tr/2008/07/06/haber,D299C6C2ACD84E78A8AC6E518A111995.html Adnan Polat: We're not selling Arda]</ref>

Since the European championships, [[AC Milan]], [[Juventus]], [[Everton F.C.]]<ref>[http://www.skysports.com/story/0,19528,11095_3738821,00.html: Turan set for Serie A]</ref> [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]]<ref>[http://www.eyefootball.com/news/6491/Arsenal-chase-Arda-Turan/ Arsenal chase Arda Turan]</ref> and [[Bayern Munich]],<ref>[http://www.transfermarketweb.com/index.php?action=read&idsel=32610: Bayern Munich keen on Arda Turan]</ref> have all shown an interest in him.

==International career==
Arda is an international regular having made over 30 appearances for [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] at senior level. He made his debut in the 2&ndash;0 friendly victory over [[Luxembourg national football team|Luxembourg]] in August 2006, having worked his way through the youth National Team at U19 and U21 level. He scored his first international goal on May 25, 2008 in a friendly against [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]].

===Euro 2008===
Arda featured in nine of Turkey's twelve qualification matches for [[UEFA Euro 2008|Euro 2008]], and starred in the finals of the tournament itself. He scored two goals during [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s progression to the semi-finals. The first was a 92nd minute winner against the [[Switzerland national football team|Swiss]] in their second group game to knock them out of the competition. His second came in the final group game against the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic]], in which the winner would go through to the quarter-finals due to identical records. He scored Turkey's first goal in the 75th minute, beating [[Petr Cech]] with a low shot, which lead to Turkey coming from 2-0 down to win the match. He also successfully converted a spot-kick in the penalty shootout against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] in the quarter-finals, taking Turkey to the semi's.

